// Dynamic Programming Concept:
//
// Dynamic programming (DP) is an optimization technique where
// we solve complex problems by breaking them into smaller overlapping subproblems,
// storing results to avoid redundant computation.
//
// In Maximum Subarray Problem:
// - We use DP to track the maximum subarray ending at each index.
// - We build the solution bottom-up using previous results (Kadane's Algorithm).
